{% set father = 'CertUnlpNgenBundle:ExternalIncident:Report/Twig/BaseReport/baseReport.'~txtOrHtml~'.twig' %}
{% extends father %}{% block problem %}

We would like to inform you that we have been notified that the <em>host</em> {{incident.hostAddress}} is providing insecure <strong>Network Time Protocol</strong> (NTP) service by responding to <a href="https://www.us-cert.gov/ncas/alerts/TA14-013A">NTP monlist</a> commands.

{% endblock %}


{% block derivated_problem_content %}


<p class="lead">Related issues</p>

The <em>host</em> under your administration could be used to perform <a href="https://www.us-cert.gov/ncas/alerts/TA14-017A">amplification</a> attacks to third party's, like:

<ul>
<li><p>Denial of Service attacks (DOS, DDOS).</p></li>
</ul>

{% endblock %}


{% block verification_content %}


<p class="lead">How to verify the issue</p>

To manually verify if the service is vulnerable, use the following command:


<div class = "destacated">

<pre><code>ntpdc -n -c monlist {{incident.hostAddress}}
</code></pre>

</div>


{% endblock %}


{% block recommendations_content %}


<p class="lead">Recommendations</p>

Versions of  <code>ntpd</code> previous to 4.2.7 are vulnerable. Therefore, we recommend upgrading to the latest version available.
If upgrading is not possible, as an alternative disable <code>monlist</code>.


{% endblock %}


{% block more_information_content %}

